# sensitive-patterns — content the pre-commit hook will flag in staged diffs.
# One POSIX extended regex per line (`grep -E` flavor). Comments start with #.
# Blank lines are ignored.
#
# When a staged line you're adding matches any of these, the commit is blocked
# and a dialog (macOS) + terminal output tells you exactly what was hit.
# You then choose:
#   1. KEEP IT BLOCKED — do nothing.
#   2. SCRUB IT — edit the file, re-stage, commit again.
#   3. ACCEPT IT — `git commit --no-verify` for this one commit.
#
# Design principle: patterns should be NARROW. Catching "every email" or
# "every IPv4" creates so many false positives that you'll train yourself to
# --no-verify reflexively, which defeats the purpose.
#
# Below are templates — replace with values that apply to you.

# ---- Real names you don't want leaking through doc/code drift ----
# Use full phrases to avoid catching unrelated brands.
# Example:
#   John Doe
#   J\. Doe

# ---- Client / contact names ----
# Add a new line per client surname or full name as relationships form.
# Example:
#   Smith
#   Alice Brown

# ---- Personal email addresses ----
# DELIBERATELY commented out by default — your own email often appears in
# legitimate places (product support contact, n8n notification recipients,
# auto-synced dashboards). Add CLIENT or third-party emails here instead.
# Example:
#   client\.surname@example\.com

# ---- Phone numbers (your country / area code) ----
# Example (Sweden):
#   \+46[0-9 -]{8,}

# ---- Local filesystem paths that reveal username or folder structure ----
# These nearly always leak when AI assistants paste install instructions.
/Users/[a-z0-9_-]+
/home/[a-z0-9_-]+
~/Desktop/
~/Downloads/

# ---- Invoice / financial document IDs ----
# Example:
#   INV-20[0-9]{2}-[0-9]+
#   FAKTURA-?[0-9]+

# ---- Specific public IPs you don't want exposed (VPS, homelab, etc.) ----
# Add each as a literal — a broad IPv4 regex would catch 127.0.0.1 and break
# every commit that mentions localhost.
# Example:
#   62\.238\.38\.28

# ---- High-signal secret markers (uncomment if you want them caught) ----
# OPENAI_API_KEY
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
# password\s*=\s*['\"][^'\"]{4,}
